[CLAUDE] # Bug Tracker — System Overview
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Bug Tracker is a Next.js 16 application for teams to capture, triage, and manage software issues inside an authenticated, multi-tenant workspace.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Core Capabilities
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Capability | Description |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|
[CLAUDE] | Bug management | Create, update, bulk-update, archive bugs with comments and file attachments |
[CLAUDE] | Projects & sections | Bugs are scoped to projects; projects contain ordered sections |
[CLAUDE] | Organizations | Multi-tenant — users belong to organizations, each with its own data |
[CLAUDE] | Authentication | Session-based auth with email verification, password reset, and JWT API keys |
[CLAUDE] | Notifications | Email delivery via SendGrid for bug lifecycle events |
[CLAUDE] | Monitoring | Operational logs, error fingerprinting, grouped errors, endpoint performance |
[CLAUDE] | Admin panel | Admin-only surfaces for users, projects, notifications, monitoring, bug data I/O |
[CLAUDE] | Agent API | REST endpoints for automated bug operations (claim, update status) |
[CLAUDE] | MCP server | Model Context Protocol server for LLM-based agent integration |
[CLAUDE] | Chrome extension | Browser extension for in-page bug reporting |
[CLAUDE] | Bug data I/O | CSV import and export with job queue and status tracking |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Technology Stack
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] - **Runtime**: Node.js + Next.js 16 (App Router, webpack mode)
[CLAUDE] - **Language**: TypeScript
[CLAUDE] - **Database**: PostgreSQL (primary); in-memory SQLite for fast unit tests
[CLAUDE] - **UI**: React 19, Tailwind CSS v4, shadcn/ui components
[CLAUDE] - **Email**: SendGrid
[CLAUDE] - **Validation**: Zod v4
[CLAUDE] - **Testing**: Node built-in test runner + Playwright for E2E
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## High-Level Architecture
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ```
[CLAUDE] Browser / Extension
[CLAUDE]        │
[CLAUDE]   Next.js App Router
[CLAUDE]   ┌────┴────────────────────────────────────┐
[CLAUDE]   │  src/app/                               │
[CLAUDE]   │  ├── (authenticated)/   UI routes       │
[CLAUDE]   │  ├── api/               API handlers    │
[CLAUDE]   │  └── layout / auth pages               │
[CLAUDE]   └─────────────────┬───────────────────────┘
[CLAUDE]                     │
[CLAUDE]             src/lib/ (domain services)
[CLAUDE]             ├── auth/         Authentication & sessions
[CLAUDE]             ├── bugs/         Bug domain + agent + MCP
[CLAUDE]             ├── organizations/ Multi-tenancy
[CLAUDE]             ├── projects/     Project & section management
[CLAUDE]             ├── notifications/ Email dispatch
[CLAUDE]             ├── monitoring/   Observability & alerts
[CLAUDE]             ├── settings/     API keys & JWT config
[CLAUDE]             └── db/           Database abstraction
[CLAUDE]                     │
[CLAUDE]           PostgreSQL (primary)
[CLAUDE]           In-memory DB (tests)
[CLAUDE] ```
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Key Entry Points
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Path | Purpose |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|
[CLAUDE] | `src/app/(authenticated)/` | All authenticated UI pages |
[CLAUDE] | `src/app/api/` | REST API route handlers |
[CLAUDE] | `src/lib/bugs/` | Core bug domain logic |
[CLAUDE] | `src/lib/monitoring/` | Observability stack |
[CLAUDE] | `src/lib/notifications/` | Email notification system |
[CLAUDE] | `scripts/` | CLI tools: bug agent, alerts, MCP server |
[CLAUDE] 
