[CLAUDE] # API Endpoints Reference
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] All handlers are wrapped with `withRequestObservability` which logs request timing and errors to the operational log.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Authentication — `/api/auth/*`
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Method | Path | Description |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|---|
[CLAUDE] | POST | `/api/auth/signup` | Register user + create organization; sets session cookie |
[CLAUDE] | POST | `/api/auth/login` | Authenticate with email/password; sets session cookie |
[CLAUDE] | POST | `/api/auth/logout` | Invalidate session cookie |
[CLAUDE] | GET | `/api/auth/session` | Return current session info |
[CLAUDE] | POST | `/api/auth/verify-email` | Consume email verification token |
[CLAUDE] | POST | `/api/auth/forgot-password` | Send password reset email |
[CLAUDE] | POST | `/api/auth/reset-password` | Consume reset token and set new password |
[CLAUDE] | POST | `/api/auth/change-password` | Change password for authenticated user |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Session is stored in a cookie (`getSessionCookieName()`). The Extension uses `Authorization: Bearer` header instead.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Bugs — `/api/bugs/*`
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Method | Path | Description |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|---|
[CLAUDE] | GET | `/api/bugs` | List bugs (filterable by project, status, reporter, dates, sort) |
[CLAUDE] | POST | `/api/bugs` | Create a bug |
[CLAUDE] | GET | `/api/bugs/[bugId]` | Get single bug |
[CLAUDE] | PATCH | `/api/bugs/[bugId]` | Update bug fields (title, description, severity, status, assignee, project, section, archived) |
[CLAUDE] | PATCH | `/api/bugs/bulk` | Bulk update bug statuses |
[CLAUDE] | GET | `/api/bugs/[bugId]/comments` | List comments |
[CLAUDE] | POST | `/api/bugs/[bugId]/comments` | Add comment (with optional visibility) |
[CLAUDE] | POST | `/api/bugs/[bugId]/attachments` | Upload attachment |
[CLAUDE] | GET | `/api/bugs/[bugId]/attachments/[attachmentId]` | Download attachment |
[CLAUDE] | DELETE | `/api/bugs/[bugId]/attachments/[attachmentId]` | Delete attachment |
[CLAUDE] | GET | `/api/bugs/[bugId]/history` | List change history (org admin only) |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Agent API — `/api/agent/*`
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Authenticated via agent API key. Used by automated agents.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Method | Path | Description |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|---|
[CLAUDE] | GET | `/api/agent/bugs` | List claimable bugs |
[CLAUDE] | GET | `/api/agent/bugs/[bugId]` | Get bug detail |
[CLAUDE] | POST | `/api/agent/bugs/[bugId]/claim` | Claim a bug (`claimedBy` string required) |
[CLAUDE] | PATCH | `/api/agent/bugs/[bugId]/status` | Update agent work state (`claimedBy`, `state`, `statusNote`) |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Admin — `/api/admin/*`
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] All endpoints require admin role (`requireAdminUser`).
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ### Projects
[CLAUDE] | Method | Path | Description |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|---|
[CLAUDE] | GET/POST | `/api/admin/projects` | List / create projects |
[CLAUDE] | PATCH | `/api/admin/projects/[projectId]` | Update project (name, key, description, isArchived) |
[CLAUDE] | GET/POST | `/api/admin/projects/[projectId]/sections` | List / create sections |
[CLAUDE] | PATCH | `/api/admin/projects/[projectId]/sections/[sectionId]` | Update section |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ### Users
[CLAUDE] | Method | Path | Description |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|---|
[CLAUDE] | GET/POST | `/api/admin/users` | List / create QA users |
[CLAUDE] | POST | `/api/admin/users/[userId]/deactivate` | Deactivate QA user |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ### Monitoring
[CLAUDE] | Method | Path | Description |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|---|
[CLAUDE] | GET | `/api/admin/logs` | Paginated operational logs (filterable by severity) |
[CLAUDE] | GET | `/api/admin/errors` | Grouped error fingerprints |
[CLAUDE] | PATCH | `/api/admin/errors/[fingerprint]/bug` | Link error group to a bug |
[CLAUDE] | GET | `/api/admin/alerts` | List operational alerts |
[CLAUDE] | GET/PATCH | `/api/admin/alerts/[alertId]` | Get / update alert status |
[CLAUDE] | POST | `/api/admin/alerts/[alertId]/bugs` | Create bug from alert |
[CLAUDE] | GET | `/api/admin/performance/endpoints` | Endpoint performance stats |
[CLAUDE] | GET | `/api/admin/performance/org-usage` | Per-org usage stats |
[CLAUDE] | GET | `/api/admin/dashboard/summary` | Admin dashboard summary |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ### Notifications
[CLAUDE] | Method | Path | Description |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|---|
[CLAUDE] | GET/PATCH | `/api/admin/notifications/settings` | List / update notification settings |
[CLAUDE] | GET | `/api/admin/notifications/deliveries` | Delivery history |
[CLAUDE] | POST | `/api/admin/notifications/deliveries/[deliveryId]/retry` | Retry failed delivery |
[CLAUDE] | POST | `/api/admin/notifications/events/[eventId]/retry` | Retry failed event |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Extension API — `/api/extension/*`
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Separate auth flow using `Authorization: Bearer` token (not cookies).
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Method | Path | Description |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|---|
[CLAUDE] | POST | `/api/extension/auth/login` | Login, returns token |
[CLAUDE] | POST | `/api/extension/auth/logout` | Invalidate token |
[CLAUDE] | GET | `/api/extension/auth/session` | Get current session |
[CLAUDE] | GET | `/api/extension/projects` | List projects |
[CLAUDE] | GET | `/api/extension/version` | Extension compatibility check |
[CLAUDE] | POST | `/api/extension/bugs/[bugId]/evidence` | Upload evidence during testing session |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Observability — `/api/observability/*`
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Method | Path | Description |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|---|
[CLAUDE] | POST | `/api/observability/page-load` | Record client-side page load metrics |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Error Response Pattern
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] API errors follow this pattern based on the service error class thrown:
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Error Class | HTTP Status |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|
[CLAUDE] | `AuthenticationError` | 401 |
[CLAUDE] | `ActiveOrganizationSessionError` | 403 |
[CLAUDE] | `BugServiceError` | 400 / 404 |
[CLAUDE] | `ProjectServiceError` | 400 / 404 |
[CLAUDE] | `OperationalAlertServiceError` | 400 / 404 |
[CLAUDE] | Unhandled | 500 |
