[CLAUDE] # Database Schema
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] The app supports two database backends selected via the `BUG_TRACKER_TEST_DB_BACKEND` env var:
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] - **`postgres`** — production backend using `pg` driver; schema defined in `src/lib/db/postgres-schema.ts`
[CLAUDE] - **`memory`** — in-memory SQLite-compatible store used for unit tests (no Docker needed)
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] The abstraction layer in `src/lib/db/database-client.ts` exposes a unified `DatabaseClient` interface to all services.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Migration
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Migrations run against PostgreSQL only:
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ```bash
[CLAUDE] npm run db:migrate:postgres
[CLAUDE] ```
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] This executes `scripts/migrate-postgres.ts` using `.env` for connection details.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Core Tables (inferred from services and schema)
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ### users
[CLAUDE] Stores workspace users. Created during signup or by admins as QA users.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Column | Notes |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|
[CLAUDE] | id | PK |
[CLAUDE] | name | Display name |
[CLAUDE] | email | Unique, used for login |
[CLAUDE] | password_hash | Bcrypt hash |
[CLAUDE] | is_admin | Admin flag |
[CLAUDE] | is_verified | Email verified flag |
[CLAUDE] | created_at / updated_at | Timestamps |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ### organizations
[CLAUDE] Top-level tenant boundary. Created at signup.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Column | Notes |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|
[CLAUDE] | id | PK |
[CLAUDE] | name | Display name |
[CLAUDE] | slug | URL-safe unique identifier |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ### organization_members
[CLAUDE] Many-to-many: users ↔ organizations with role.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ### projects
[CLAUDE] Scoped to an organization.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Column | Notes |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|
[CLAUDE] | id | PK |
[CLAUDE] | organization_id | FK → organizations |
[CLAUDE] | name, key | Identifiers |
[CLAUDE] | description | Optional |
[CLAUDE] | is_archived | Soft delete |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ### project_sections
[CLAUDE] Ordered sub-groupings within a project.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Column | Notes |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|
[CLAUDE] | id | PK |
[CLAUDE] | project_id | FK → projects |
[CLAUDE] | name | Section label |
[CLAUDE] | display_order | Integer for ordering |
[CLAUDE] | is_archived | Soft delete |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ### bugs
[CLAUDE] Core entity.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Column | Notes |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|
[CLAUDE] | id | PK |
[CLAUDE] | organization_id | FK → organizations |
[CLAUDE] | project_id | FK → projects |
[CLAUDE] | section_id | FK → project_sections (nullable) |
[CLAUDE] | title | Short description |
[CLAUDE] | description | Full detail |
[CLAUDE] | severity | Enum (see domain model) |
[CLAUDE] | status | Enum: New / Triaged / In Progress / Ready for QA / Closed |
[CLAUDE] | reporter_user_id | FK → users |
[CLAUDE] | assignee_user_id | FK → users (nullable) |
[CLAUDE] | is_archived | Boolean |
[CLAUDE] | agent_state | Agent claim state (nullable) |
[CLAUDE] | claimed_by | Agent identifier string (nullable) |
[CLAUDE] | created_at / updated_at | Timestamps |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ### bug_comments
[CLAUDE] | Column | Notes |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|
[CLAUDE] | id | PK |
[CLAUDE] | bug_id | FK → bugs |
[CLAUDE] | author_user_id | FK → users |
[CLAUDE] | body | Comment text |
[CLAUDE] | visibility | `internal` / `external` |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ### bug_attachments
[CLAUDE] | Column | Notes |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|
[CLAUDE] | id | PK |
[CLAUDE] | bug_id | FK → bugs |
[CLAUDE] | file_path | Path in attachment storage |
[CLAUDE] | original_filename | Original upload name |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ### bug_history
[CLAUDE] Audit trail of all field changes on a bug.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Column | Notes |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|
[CLAUDE] | id | PK |
[CLAUDE] | bug_id | FK → bugs |
[CLAUDE] | event_type | e.g. `bug_created`, `bug_status_changed`, `bug_import_created` |
[CLAUDE] | changed_by_user_id | FK → users (nullable — system events) |
[CLAUDE] | changed_fields | JSONB array of `{field, previousValue, nextValue}` |
[CLAUDE] | created_at | Timestamp |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ### operational_logs
[CLAUDE] Application log sink for observability events.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Column | Notes |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|
[CLAUDE] | id | PK |
[CLAUDE] | severity | `debug` / `info` / `warn` / `error` / `critical` |
[CLAUDE] | message | Log line |
[CLAUDE] | context | JSONB metadata |
[CLAUDE] | created_at | Timestamp |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ### operational_alerts
[CLAUDE] Aggregated alerts derived from error patterns.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Column | Notes |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|
[CLAUDE] | id | PK |
[CLAUDE] | grouping_key | Error fingerprint |
[CLAUDE] | severity | Alert severity |
[CLAUDE] | status | `open` / `acknowledged` / `resolved` |
[CLAUDE] | source | Origin system |
[CLAUDE] | latest_seen_at | Last occurrence timestamp |
[CLAUDE] | linked_bug_id | FK → bugs (nullable) |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ### notifications
[CLAUDE] Tracks email notification events and deliveries.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ### auth_action_tokens
[CLAUDE] Short-lived tokens for email verification and password reset.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ### api_keys / auth_jwt_config
[CLAUDE] Settings for API key and JWT authentication.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ### bug_data_jobs
[CLAUDE] Import/export job queue records.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Column | Notes |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|
[CLAUDE] | id | PK |
[CLAUDE] | organization_id | FK → organizations |
[CLAUDE] | job_type | `import` / `export` |
[CLAUDE] | status | `queued` / `running` / `completed` / `completed_with_warnings` / `failed` |
[CLAUDE] | source_file_name | Original filename for imports |
[CLAUDE] | result_file_path | Output path for exports |
[CLAUDE] | summary | JSONB job summary metrics |
[CLAUDE] | warnings / errors | JSONB arrays |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## PostgreSQL Worker
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Some database operations run in a separate worker thread (`src/lib/db/postgres-worker.ts`) to avoid blocking the main thread. The worker bundle is built separately:
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ```bash
[CLAUDE] npm run build:db-worker   # outputs to .next/db/postgres-worker.mjs
[CLAUDE] ```
