[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # Deployment & Setup
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Local Development (First Run)
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ```bash
[CLAUDE] # 1. Clone and install
[CLAUDE] cp .env.example .env
[CLAUDE] npm install
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # 2. Start PostgreSQL
[CLAUDE] docker compose up -d postgres
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # 3. Run migrations
[CLAUDE] npm run db:migrate:postgres
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # 4. Start dev server (predev builds the DB worker automatically)
[CLAUDE] npm run dev
[CLAUDE] # → http://localhost:3000
[CLAUDE] ```
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] The `predev` hook runs `build:db-worker` before the Next.js dev server starts.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Environment Variables
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Copy `.env.example` to `.env`. Key variables:
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Variable | Required | Notes |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|---|
[CLAUDE] | `DATABASE_URL` | Yes | PostgreSQL connection string (`127.0.0.1:5432` default) |
[CLAUDE] | `SENDGRID_API_KEY` | Optional | Leave empty for local dev without email |
[CLAUDE] | `SESSION_SECRET` | Yes | Secret for signing session cookies |
[CLAUDE] | `NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL` | Yes | Base URL used in email links |
[CLAUDE] | `BUG_TRACKER_TEST_DB_BACKEND` | Test only | `memory` (default for tests) or `postgres` |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Production Build
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ```bash
[CLAUDE] npm run build          # Next.js build + DB worker bundle
[CLAUDE] npm run start          # Start production server
[CLAUDE] ```
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] The build produces:
[CLAUDE] - `.next/` — Next.js output
[CLAUDE] - `.next/db/postgres-worker.mjs` — standalone PostgreSQL worker
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Nginx Reverse Proxy
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] See `docs/deployment-nginx.md` for domain-based setup with Nginx in front of `next start`.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Typical configuration proxies `localhost:3000` and handles:
[CLAUDE] - TLS termination
[CLAUDE] - Static asset caching
[CLAUDE] - WebSocket upgrade (if needed)
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Docker Compose
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `compose.yaml` defines at minimum a `postgres` service. The app itself is not containerized by default — it runs directly on the host via `npm run start`.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Database Migrations
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Migrations are applied manually before starting the app:
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ```bash
[CLAUDE] npm run db:migrate:postgres
[CLAUDE] ```
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] There is no auto-migration on startup. Run this after every deployment that includes schema changes.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## CLI Tools (scripts/)
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Script | Command | Purpose |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|---|
[CLAUDE] | `scripts/bug-agent-cli.ts` | `npm run bugs:cli` | Agent CLI for bug operations |
[CLAUDE] | `scripts/alerts-cli.ts` | `npm run alerts:cli` | Alerts management CLI |
[CLAUDE] | `scripts/mcp-server.ts` | `npm run mcp:server` | Start MCP server for LLM agent integration |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Observability Output
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Structured logs are written to `log/observability.ndjson` (NDJSON format). See `docs/observability.md` and the [Monitoring page](../monitoring.md) for details.
[CLAUDE] === END FILE ===
