[CLAUDE] ---
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # ADR-002: Technology Stack
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Decisions
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ### Next.js App Router (not Pages Router)
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] All routes use the App Router pattern with route handlers (`route.ts` files) for APIs and React Server Components for UI.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Webpack mode is used explicitly (`next dev --webpack`, `next build --webpack`) rather than Turbopack — likely for compatibility with specific Node.js addons (e.g. `pg` native bindings) or build plugins.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ### TypeScript Throughout
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Both frontend and backend are TypeScript. No JavaScript files in `src/`. `tsconfig.json` enforces strict checks via `npm run typecheck`.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ### PostgreSQL Worker Thread
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] The `pg` client runs in a dedicated worker thread (`postgres-worker.ts`) to avoid blocking the Node.js event loop during heavy queries. This is bundled separately via esbuild.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ### Zod for Validation
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Runtime validation at API boundaries uses Zod v4. Type inference from schemas feeds TypeScript types.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ### shadcn/ui Component Library
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] UI components under `src/components/ui/` are shadcn/ui components (Radix primitives + Tailwind). These are copied into the repo (not a runtime dependency) and can be customised freely.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ### SendGrid for Email
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Transactional email via SendGrid. No self-hosted SMTP. The integration is optional for local development.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ### Node Built-in Test Runner
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Tests use `node --test` (no Jest or Vitest). This avoids a heavy test framework dependency and works natively in Node 22+.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ### Playwright for E2E
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] End-to-end tests use `@playwright/test`. A separate seeded test database is used for E2E runs on port 3001.
[CLAUDE] === END FILE ===
[CLAUDE] 
