[CLAUDE] ---
[CLAUDE] type: decision
[CLAUDE] owner: engineering
[CLAUDE] last_updated: 2026-04-20
[CLAUDE] source_count: 6
[CLAUDE] tags: [observability, logging, monitoring]
[CLAUDE] status: active
[CLAUDE] ---
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # ADR-003: Built-In Observability Stack
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Decision
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] The app implements its own observability stack (operational logs, error fingerprinting, grouped errors, alerts, performance metrics) stored in PostgreSQL rather than relying on an external APM service.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Rationale
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] **Why:** Keeps the deployment simple — no Datadog/Sentry/New Relic accounts required. The admin panel provides a first-class UI for logs, errors, and alerts without leaving the application.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] **How to apply:** New API routes should always be wrapped with `withRequestObservability`. Significant business events should be logged via `ObservabilityLoggerService`. Do not add external APM agents without a clear decision to do so.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Components
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Component | Purpose |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|
[CLAUDE] | `withRequestObservability` | Middleware wrapping all API handlers |
[CLAUDE] | `ObservabilityLoggerService` | Structured log emission |
[CLAUDE] | `ObservabilityFileSink` | NDJSON log file for external ingestion |
[CLAUDE] | `ObservabilityRedaction` | Strips PII/secrets before persistence |
[CLAUDE] | `ErrorFingerprint` | Stable hash for error deduplication |
[CLAUDE] | `GroupedErrorsService` | Aggregates errors by fingerprint |
[CLAUDE] | `OperationalAlertService` | Higher-level alert management |
[CLAUDE] | `EndpointPerformanceService` | Response time tracking |
[CLAUDE] | `PageLoadObservability` | Client-side metric collection |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## File Output
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Logs are also written to `log/observability.ndjson` in NDJSON format, enabling external log shippers (Loki, CloudWatch, etc.) to ingest them without database access.
[CLAUDE] === END FILE ===
[CLAUDE] 
