[CLAUDE] ---
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # Email Notifications
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Overview
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] All transactional email is delivered via **SendGrid**. The notification pipeline handles event routing, recipient resolution, template rendering, and delivery tracking.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Pipeline
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ```
[CLAUDE] Bug/Auth Event
[CLAUDE]   └── bug-notification-event-service.ts   — emit notification event
[CLAUDE]        └── notification-dispatcher.ts      — route to recipient groups
[CLAUDE]             └── bug-recipient-service.ts   — resolve recipient list
[CLAUDE]                  └── template-engine.ts    — render HTML template
[CLAUDE]                       └── sendgrid-delivery.ts — deliver via SendGrid API
[CLAUDE]                            └── notification-store.ts — record delivery
[CLAUDE] ```
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Notification Events
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Events triggered by bug lifecycle:
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Event | Template |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|
[CLAUDE] | Bug created | `bug-created.html` |
[CLAUDE] | Bug assigned | `bug-assigned.html` |
[CLAUDE] | Bug status changed | `bug-status-changed.html` |
[CLAUDE] | Bug comment added | `bug-comment.html` |
[CLAUDE] | Bug closed | `bug-closed.html` |
[CLAUDE] | Bug reopened | `bug-reopened.html` |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Auth notification templates:
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Event | Template |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|
[CLAUDE] | Signup welcome | `welcome.html` |
[CLAUDE] | Email verification | `verification.html` |
[CLAUDE] | Forgot password | `forgot-password.html` |
[CLAUDE] | Password reset complete | `password-reset-complete.html` |
[CLAUDE] | Password changed | `password-changed.html` |
[CLAUDE] | Organization invitation | `organization-invitation.html` |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] All templates extend `base-layout.html` via the template engine.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Template Engine
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `template-engine.ts` renders HTML templates with variable substitution. Templates live in `src/lib/notifications/templates/`.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `email-template-registry.ts` maps event types to template files.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Admin Features
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Via `notification-admin-service.ts`:
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] - `listNotificationDeliveryHistory()` — paginated delivery log
[CLAUDE] - `retryNotificationDeliveryForAdmin()` — retry a failed delivery
[CLAUDE] - `retryNotificationEvent()` — replay a notification event
[CLAUDE] - `listNotificationSettingsSummary()` / `updateNotificationSettings()` — enable/disable notification types per recipient group
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Configuration
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] SendGrid API key is set via environment variables. Leave empty for local development when not testing email flows.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Test endpoint available at `/api/test/sendgrid` (development only).
[CLAUDE] === END FILE ===
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] === FILE: wiki/systems/bug_tracker/organizations/multi-tenancy.md ===
[CLAUDE] ---
[CLAUDE] type: system
[CLAUDE] owner: engineering
[CLAUDE] last_updated: 2026-04-20
[CLAUDE] source_count: 10
[CLAUDE] tags: [organizations, multi-tenancy, membership, invitations, billing]
[CLAUDE] status: active
[CLAUDE] ---
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # Organizations & Multi-Tenancy
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Model
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Each user belongs to one or more **Organizations**. All data (bugs, projects, settings) is scoped to an organization.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] A user has one **active organization** per session, managed via `active-organization-session.ts`.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Organization Lifecycle
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] 1. **Creation**: Org is created during signup (`registerUserWithOrganization()`)
[CLAUDE] 2. **Onboarding**: Additional setup via `/onboarding` flow
[CLAUDE] 3. **Switching**: Users switch between orgs; active org stored in session
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Membership
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Service | Purpose |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|
[CLAUDE] | `organization-membership-service.ts` | Add/remove members, role management |
[CLAUDE] | `organization-access-service.ts` | Access checks: `requireOrganizationAdminAccessForUser()` |
[CLAUDE] | `organization-seat-service.ts` | Seat count enforcement |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Invitations
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Flow:
[CLAUDE] 1. Admin sends invitation → `organization-invitation-service.ts` creates token
[CLAUDE] 2. Email sent via `organization-invitation-email-service.ts`
[CLAUDE] 3. Invitee lands on `/invitations/[invitationId]` 
[CLAUDE] 4. Accepts via `organization-invitation-activation-service.ts`
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] API routes: `/api/invitations/*`, `/api/organizations/invitations`
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Projects Within Organizations
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Each project belongs to an organization. Project access is additionally controlled at the project level.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `project-access-context.ts` provides UI content when a user lacks project access.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Billing
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `organization-billing-service.ts` manages billing state. UI in `organization-billing-panel.tsx` at `/billing`.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `billing-ui.ts` provides presentation helpers.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Active Organization Session
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `requireActiveOrganizationSession()` is used by all bug-facing API routes to ensure a valid org context. This guard appears in all `/api/bugs/*` handlers.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Audit Log
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] All significant org actions are logged via `organization-audit-log-service.ts` / `organization-audit-log-store.ts`.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Accessible at `/organization/audit` in the UI.
[CLAUDE] === END FILE ===
[CLAUDE] 
